    %h1 &Pi;
  :markdown
    I'm an Associate Professor of Philosophy at [NYU Shanghai][nyush], Global Network Professor of [Philosophy][nyu-phil] at [New York University][nyu], and a Guest Professor of Philosophy at [East China Normal University][ecnu].  I work in philosophy of science, especially causation and explanation, and on related topics in philosophy of physics, philosophy of biology and philosophy of mind.
    
    #### selected publications

    - “A Partial Theory of Actual Causation”, in *The British Journal for the Philosophy of Science*, *forthcoming*. <span class="sc">\[[pdf](http://goo.gl/tpW8kx)\]</span>
    - “Difference-Making, Closure and Exclusion”, in Helen Beebee, Chris Hitchcock and Huw Price (Eds), *Making a Difference: Essays on the Philosophy of Causation*, Oxford University Press, Oxford, 2017, pp. 215–231. <span class="sc">\[[pdf](http://goo.gl/XmEyby)\]</span> 
    - “Statistical Mechanical Imperialism”, in Alastair Wilson (Ed), *Chance and Temporal Asymmetry*, Oxford University Press, Oxford, 2014, pp. 241–257. <span class="sc">\[[pdf](http://goo.gl/EUiAm)\]</span>
    - “Proportionality, Contrast and Explanation”, in *Australasian Journal of Philosophy*, <span class="sc">vol</span>. 91, <span class="sc">no</span>. 4, 2013, pp. 785–797. <span class="sc">\[[pdf](http://goo.gl/iAB3v)\]</span>
    - “Explanatory Depth”, in *Philosophy of Science*, <span class="sc">vol</span>. 77, <span class="sc">no</span>. 2, <span class="sc">apr</span> 2010, pp. 273–294. <span class="sc">\[[pdf](http://goo.gl/rS1DVw)\]</span> 
    - “The Time-Asymmetry of Causation” (with [Huw Price][huw]), in Helen Beebee, Chris Hitchcock and Peter Menzies (Eds), *Oxford Handbook of Causation*, Oxford University Press, Oxford, 2009, pp. 414–443. <span class="sc">\[[pdf](http://goo.gl/cZd6HC)\]</span> 

